          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reflexion: Verbal Reinforcement Learning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reflexion (Shinn et al., 2023) is a framework that enables agents to improve across trials using natural language feedback stored in episodic memory \u2014 without gradient updates or fine-tuning. When a trial fails, a Self-Reflector LLM analyses the trajectory and writes a verbal lesson. The next trial's Actor reads that lesson as context, avoiding the same mistakes. Three components \u2014 Actor, Evaluator, and Self-Reflector \u2014 work together to implement this verbal reinforcement loop."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Reflexion Architecture: Actor, Evaluator, Self-Reflector, Episodic Memory",
          "title": ""
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Reflexion replaces gradient descent with language. Instead of updating weights, the agent writes down what went wrong and reads that note before the next attempt."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
