      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reflection Quality: What Makes a Good Lesson"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The quality of the Self-Reflector's output determines whether Reflexion actually improves performance. Vague lessons ('Try harder next time') provide no actionable guidance. Effective lessons are specific, attributable to a concrete step in the trajectory, and phrased as instructions the Actor can follow immediately."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Poor reflection \u2014 too vague to act on\npoor = (\n    \"You failed to solve the task. Try to be more careful next time \"\n    \"and pay attention to the details.\"\n)\n\n# Good reflection \u2014 specific, attributable, actionable\ngood = (\n    \"You called search() with the full sentence as the query, which returned no results. \"\n    \"Next time, extract only the key noun phrase (e.g. the person's name or the item) \"\n    \"and use that as the search query. Verify results are non-empty before proceeding.\"\n)\n\n# Enforce quality with a validation check\nREFLECTION_QUALITY_PROMPT = \"\"\"Is this reflection specific enough to be actionable?\nReflection: {reflection}\nAnswer with JSON: {{\"actionable\": bool, \"reason\": str}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef validate_reflection(\n    client,\n    reflection: str,\n) -> bool:\n    import json, re\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=128,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\n            REFLECTION_QUALITY_PROMPT.format(reflection=reflection)}],\n    )\n    m = re.search(r\"\\{.*\\}\", resp.content[0].text, re.DOTALL)\n    data = json.loads(m.group()) if m else {}\n    return bool(data.get(\"actionable\", True))\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reflexion with Tool Use"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the Agent has tools, the Reflexion loop extends naturally: actions are tool calls rather than free-text steps, and observations are tool results. The Self-Reflector can then reason about which tool was called, whether the arguments were appropriate, and what a better tool invocation would look like."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TOOL_REFLECT_PROMPT = \"\"\"An agent made tool calls but failed to solve the task.\n\nTask: {task}\nTools available: {tools}\n\nTool calls made:\n{tool_calls}\n\nWrite a 2-3 sentence lesson focusing on:\n- Which tool was called incorrectly (wrong tool, wrong arguments)\n- What the correct tool invocation should look like\n- Any tool that should have been called but was missed\n\"\"\"\n\ndef self_reflect_tool_use(\n    client,\n    task: str,\n    tools: list[str],\n    trial: Trial,\n) -> str:\n    tool_calls = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"  Step {i+1}: {s.action} \u2192 {s.observation[:80]}\"\n        for i, s in enumerate(trial.steps)\n    )\n    prompt = TOOL_REFLECT_PROMPT.format(\n        task=task,\n        tools=\", \".join(tools),\n        tool_calls=tool_calls,\n    )\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=256,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    return resp.content[0].text.strip()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "A tool-aware Self-Reflector can distinguish between 'you used the right tool with wrong arguments' (an argument-fixing lesson) and 'you used the wrong tool entirely' (a tool-selection lesson) \u2014 producing much more targeted guidance for the next trial."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
